    <section class="page-1 section-8 sr-story-main sr-last" id="909928">
        <article class="sr-story clearfix" data-id="909928" data-url="/speedreads/909928/world-bank-predicts-coronavirus-push-between-40-million-60-million-people-into-poverty" data-headline="World Bank predicts coronavirus will push between 40 million and 60 million people into poverty" data-tags="[speedread,News,Business]" data-publish-date="April 20, 2020" data-authors="[Tim O'Donnell]">
            
            
                            <div class="sr-slug"><a href="/speedreads/section/coronavirus%20fallout">coronavirus fallout</a></div>
            
            <div class="sr-headline-section">
                <div class="edit-link">
	<a href="http://cms.theweek.com/admin/tw-admin/edit/909928">Edit</a>
</div>                <h2 class="sr-headline"><a href="/speedreads/909928/world-bank-predicts-coronavirus-push-between-40-million-60-million-people-into-poverty">World Bank predicts coronavirus will push between 40 million and 60 million people into poverty</a></h2>
            </div>

            <div class="sr-date">5:27 p.m.</div>

            <div class="sr-body-share-wrapper">
                <div class="sr-body" id="sr-body-909928">
                                            <div class="sr-image-section">
                            <a href="/speedreads/909928/world-bank-predicts-coronavirus-push-between-40-million-60-million-people-into-poverty" tabindex="-1">
                                    
    
                
        
                

                
                
                
                
        
    <picture class="picture-wrapper sr-image">    <source srcset="" type="image/webp"/>        <img class="picture webpLazyInView" alt="World Bank." src="/bundles/twsite/images/empty-src.png" data-image="https://images.theweek.com/sites/default/files/styles/tw_image_6_4/public/gettyimages-74099662.jpg?itok=FjlGrlXZ&resize=180x180"
                                            />
    </picture>
                                <div class="sr-image-credit"> Win McNamee/Getty Images</div>                            </a>
                        </div>
                    
                    <div class="sr-text">
                         <p>The World Bank is predicting a rise in global poverty in 2020 as a result of the coronavirus pandemic. If that holds true, it will be the first increase since 1998, <a href="https://www.politico.com/news/2020/04/20/world-bank-first-global-poverty-increase-196645" target="_blank"><em>Politico</em> reports</a>.</p>
<p>The international financial institution's economists <a href="https://www.politico.com/news/2020/04/20/world-bank-first-global-poverty-increase-196645" target="_blank">believe</a> the pandemic will push somewhere between 40 million and 60 million people into poverty, adding to the global rate, defined here as the percentage of the world's population living on less than $1.90 per day. The World Bank's "best estimate" is an increase of 49 million people. Sub-Saharan Africa is expected to be the region most affected.</p>
<p>Since 1998, the world has made relative progress in reducing the number of people who live in poverty, but the pandemic could wind up setting the trend back three years. "In the most pessimistic scenarios, global poverty in 2020 would be close to the level of 2017," the authors of a post on the World Bank's Data Blog <a href="https://www.politico.com/news/2020/04/20/world-bank-first-global-poverty-increase-196645" target="_blank">wrote</a>.</p>
<p>Before the pandemic, a decline in global poverty from 8.1 percent to 7.8 percent was <a href="https://www.politico.com/news/2020/04/20/world-bank-first-global-poverty-increase-196645" target="_blank">projected</a> for the year. Read more at <em><a href="https://www.politico.com/news/2020/04/20/world-bank-first-global-poverty-increase-196645" target="_blank">Politico</a></em>. <a class="author" href=/authors/tim-odonnell><em>Tim O'Donnell</em></a></p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="speedreads-share-section sr-909928">
                    <span class="fb sr-social-btn" data-url="https://theweek.com/speedreads/909928/world-bank-predicts-coronavirus-push-between-40-million-60-million-people-into-poverty" data-text="World Bank predicts coronavirus will push between 40 million and 60 million people into poverty"></span>
                    <span class="twitter sr-social-btn" data-url="https://theweek.com/speedreads/909928/world-bank-predicts-coronavirus-push-between-40-million-60-million-people-into-poverty" data-text="World Bank predicts coronavirus will push between 40 million and 60 million people into poverty" ></span>
                    <a class="email sr-social-btn" href="mailto:?subject=World Bank predicts coronavirus will push between 40 million and 60 million people into poverty&amp;body=https://theweek.com/speedreads/909928/world-bank-predicts-coronavirus-push-between-40-million-60-million-people-into-poverty" title="Share by Email" aria-label="Share by Email"></a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </article>

